{
  "stem": "985.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was still there with my father and my sister, who had married the physician.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was working in a local ambulatory for the inmates of that particular [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father was still working till the end until they took us out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all of us, we were taken by the same transport in June '44 to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, first of all, I have to mention that in Plaszow after four days, they took my father to a different camp in Wieliczka which is not far from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I never saw him after that again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my sister stayed in Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then subsequently she went to Auschwitz, Stutthof, and different camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was in Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from Plaszow, I went through Gross-Rosen to Brunnlitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's Schindler's factory.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I worked in an auto repair depot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they sent me to Brunnlitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was via Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, they sent us to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at that time there was so many transports, so many trains were coming to Auschwitz, that they had no room.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They couldn't accommodate our train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we stayed there for like a day or so.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then they switched us over to Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At Gross-Rosen, they unloaded us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they picked the ones who were on Schindler's List from Gross-Rosen and sent us to Brunnlitz, which is Czechoslovakia where Schindler--",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is the biggest puzzle of my life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody knows, not even I.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I and a friend of mine who still lives in Israel who I visited last year, we sensed there were a lot of people who had clout because they were from Krakow.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they worked for Schindler before to such a point that I had never knew at that time who was Schindler.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
